<title type="html"><![CDATA[Clarification on sound channel length counter writes]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=272&amp;p=1793#p1793"><![CDATA[
Writing to $400b doesn't reset the phase of the triangle (it can't be reset).<br /><br />Writing to $400f doesn't reset the noise shift register (it can't be reset).<br /><br />For further information about defining things in terms of what isn't, rather than what is, refer to <a href="http://home.ripway.com/2003-7/16921/deviation.mp3" class="postlink">a short tutorial on deviation</a> (300K mp3).<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=17">blargg</a> — Thu Apr 07, 2005 7:28 pm</p><hr />
]]></content>
